#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:177
msgid "Find or Create the EFI System Partition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:180
msgid ""
"On EFI based system, the bootloaders are installed in a special FAT32 "
"partition called an <emphasis>EFI System Partition</emphasis> (ESP).  If "
"your system supports EFI, and a recent version of Linux distribution or "
"Windows is pre-installed, it's likely that the ESP is already created.  As "
"the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, list all the "
"partitions on your hard drive (replace <userinput>sda</userinput> with the "
"device corresponding to the appropriate hard drive):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:190
msgid "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:193
msgid ""
"The <quote>Type</quote> column of the ESP should be <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:198
msgid ""
"If the system or the hard drive is new, or it's a first time install an UEFI"
" booted OS on the system, the ESP may not exist.  In that case, create a new"
" partition, make a <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> file "
"system on it, and set the partition type to <quote>EFI system</quote>.  See "
"the instructions for the emergency boot device above as a reference."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:208
msgid ""
"Some (old) UEFI implementations may demand the ESP to be the first partition"
" on the disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:214
msgid ""
"Now, as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, create "
"the mount point for the ESP, and mount it (replace "
"<userinput>sda1</userinput> with the device node corresponding to the ESP):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:220
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /boot/efi &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 /boot/efi</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /boot/efi &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 /boot/efi</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:224
msgid ""
"Add an entry for the ESP in <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>, so it will be "
"mounted automatically during system boot:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:229
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>/dev/sda1 /boot/efi vfat defaults 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>/dev/sda1 /boot/efi vfat defaults 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:236
msgid "Mount the EFI Variable File System"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:239
msgid ""
"The installation of GRUB on a UEFI platform requires that the EFI Variable "
"file system, <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem>, to be "
"mounted.  As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:244
msgid ""
"<userinput>mount -v -t efivarfs efivarfs "
"/sys/firmware/efi/efivars</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mount -v -t efivarfs efivarfs "
"/sys/firmware/efi/efivars</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:248
msgid ""
"If the system is booted with UEFI and systemd, <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> will be mounted automatically.  "
"However in the LFS chroot environment it still needs to be mounted manually."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:256
msgid ""
"Now add an entry for the <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">efivarfs</systemitem> in "
"<filename>/etc/fstab</filename> so it will be mounted automatically during "
"system boot:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:262
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars efivarfs defaults 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /etc/fstab &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal>efivarfs /sys/firmware/efi/efivars efivarfs defaults 0 1</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:268
msgid ""
"If the system is not booted with UEFI, the directory <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/sys/firmware/efi</filename> will be missing. In this "
"case you should boot the system in UEFI mode with the emergency boot disk "
"created as above."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:277
msgid "Setting Up the Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:280
msgid ""
"On UEFI based systems, GRUB works by installing an EFI application (a "
"special kind of executable) into <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/efi/EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</filename>, where "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/efi</filename> is the mount point of the"
" ESP, and <literal>[id]</literal> is replaced with an identifier specified "
"in the <command>grub-install</command> command line.  GRUB will create an "
"entry in the EFI variables containing the path "
"<literal>EFI/[id]/grubx64.efi</literal> so the EFI firmware can find "
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> and load it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:292
msgid ""
"<filename>grubx64.efi</filename> is very lightweight (136 KB with "
"GRUB-2.06~rc1) so it will not use much space in the ESP.  A typical ESP size"
" is 100 MB (for Windows boot manager, which uses about 50 MB in the ESP). "
"Once <filename>grubx64.efi</filename> loaded by the firmware, it will load "
"GRUB modules in the boot partition.  The default location is <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:302
msgid ""
"As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, install the "
"GRUB files into <filename>/boot/efi/EFI/LFS/grubx64.efi</filename> and "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/boot/grub</filename>. Then set up the boot "
"entry in the EFI variables:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:308
msgid "<userinput>grub-install --bootloader-id=LFS --recheck</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>grub-install --bootloader-id=LFS --recheck</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:311
msgid "If the installation is successful, the output should be:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:314
msgid ""
"<literal>Installing for x86_64-efi platform.\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>Installing for x86_64-efi platform.\n"
"Installation finished. No error reported.</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:318
msgid ""
"Issue <command>efibootmgr</command> to recheck the EFI boot configuration.  "
"An example of the output is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:322
msgid ""
"<literal>BootCurrent: 0000\n"
"Timeout: 1 seconds\n"
"BootOrder: 0005,0000,0002,0001,0003,0004\n"
"Boot0000* ARCH\n"
"Boot0001* UEFI:CD/DVD Drive\n"
"Boot0002* Windows Boot Manager\n"
"Boot0003* UEFI:Removable Device\n"
"Boot0004* UEFI:Network Device\n"
"Boot0005* LFS</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>BootCurrent: 0000\n"
"Timeout: 1 seconds\n"
"BootOrder: 0005,0000,0002,0001,0003,0004\n"
"Boot0000* ARCH\n"
"Boot0001* UEFI:CD/DVD Drive\n"
"Boot0002* Windows Boot Manager\n"
"Boot0003* UEFI:Removable Device\n"
"Boot0004* UEFI:Network Device\n"
"Boot0005* LFS</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:333
msgid ""
"Note that <literal>0005</literal> is the first in the "
"<literal>BootOrder</literal>, and <literal>Boot0005</literal> is "
"<literal>LFS</literal>. This means that on the next boot, the version of "
"GRUB installed by LFS will be used to boot the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:342
msgid "Creating the GRUB Configuration File"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><indexterm><primary>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:345
msgid "/boot/grub/grub.cfg"
msgstr "/boot/grub/grub.cfg"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:349
msgid ""
"Generate <filename>/boot/grub/grub.cfg</filename> to configure the boot menu"
" of GRUB:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:353
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
